  <front>
   <head>Carmina varia (1810) - Caesar at Rubiconem</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1">
     <l n="1">Ne quaeso transire undantia littora tentes;</l>
     <l n="2">Siste: hoc Roma potens imperat ipsa tibi.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2">
     <l n="3">Non ora haec est Aegipti verum Itala tellus:</l>
     <l n="4">Per te, Dux, an erit sanguine tincta suo?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3">
     <l n="5">Sic caput extollens Rubiconis coerulus amnis</l>
     <l n="6">Intrepido ajebat, belligeroque viro.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4">
     <l n="7">At fero trajecit vultu Mavortius heros,</l>
     <l n="8">Ac tum libertas nobilis ingemuit.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
